        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 2:47PM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 247 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Arapahoe, or 26 miles west of Holdrege, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Edison around 255 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of this storm include Hollinger.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
